metadata.name: 3ASF #43
metadata.description:
3 Armonografos Sobre Figuras / 3 Harmonographs on Shapes

"If I had to choose, the harmonograph is my preferred mechanism for making gen art"

The composition works with three harmonographs vertically distributed with 2 pendulums each that draw on black and white shapes. It is a game between the positive and the negative.

Steps-Layers:

1 - White or black background
2 - Draw shape 1 (triangle or Circle or Rectangle) with the opposite tone to the background.
3 - Draw shape 2 (triangle or Circle or Rectangle) same tone as the background.
4 - Draw the 3 Harmonographs. The (inverted) tones depend on the tones of the shapes and background.
5 - Cutting / glitch effect. Vertical and horizontal.
6 - Symmetries X or Y or XY or none are applied.
7 - Rectangles are cut again (yes/no)

// ---

metadata.name: pointillism in lines  #22
metadata.description:
This painting is drawn in pointillism style.
which includes 14 layers.
The first 10 layers contain pointillism drawings and the 11th layer is the patterns of each line.
In the 12th layer, there are 30 covers made of different geometric shapes and brushes.
And noise and frames are used in the last two layers.

metadata.name: Ephemeral Fountain v1.0 #241
metadata.description:
This project originated with me thinking about how to do very realistic glass spheres that can be manipulated and moved within the THREE.js environment. Mixing that with several hundred ephemeral non-glass objects which are moving in a fountain-like flow, adding reflection and refraction to the glass, and combining it all in a physical existence which I playfully only impose on the non-glass objects nearby... in this world, glass can move through glass, with interesting effects similar to diamonds firing when light hits them at just the right angle! 

Extremely rare to get 8 glass spheres... By the randomness imposed, 30% will have one sphere, 30% two, 20% three, 10% four, 5% five, 3% six, 1% seven and 1% eight. Happy hunting!
